M.SAL v1.0 - README [Monitor. System Authentication Logs]


Description :
This is a simple program for monitoring system authentication logs. This program create dynamic html page for show system authentication in web server. That's mean, you can open your web server ( such as http://example.com/M.SAL/ ) and see which user logged in to the server via ssh protocol and other informations like this.


Dependencies :
00. whoami
01. sleep
02. cat
03. head
04. tail
05. cut
06. awk
07. date
08. grep
09. mv
10. cp
11. rm


Check dependencies :
00. sudo chmod +x install.sh
01. sudo ./install.sh -c


Install :
00. sudo chmod +x install.sh
01. sudo ./install.sh -i


Usage :
00. sudo /opt/M.SAL_v1.0/M.SAL.sh
01. http://example.com/M.SAL/


Uninstall :
00. sudo rm -r /opt/M.SAL_v1.0/


Tested on :
00. Debian 8.1.0 netinstall - 64 Bit
01. Debian 8.4.0 netinstall - 64 Bit
02. Debian 6.0.6 netinstall - 32 Bit
03. Debian 7.8.0 netinstall - 64 Bit


Startup in system :
00. nano /etc/crontab	#Open crontab and add the following line to crontab file.
01. @reboot root /opt/M.SAL_v1.0/M.SAL.sh


Notes :
00. You have two choises : start manually or Starting up Script As a daemon
01. You should run program as root
